definition: for a particular person, occasion, purpose/focused on one thing/special/expert/particular (to sth)/concentrated/specialized
to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be

sentences.english: All rights to the Olympic symbol belong exclusively to the IOC.
sentences.chinese: 奧林匹克標誌的所有權屬國際奧委會專有。

sentences.english: B. Pick out the proper nouns in the following sentences.
sentences.chinese: 試選出以下句子中的專有名詞。

sentences.english: I have some proprietary jars that cannot be uploaded to public repos.
sentences.chinese: 我無法上傳到公開回購一些專有的罐子。

sentences.english: Proprietary drivers are drivers for your hardware which are not freely available or open-source.
sentences.chinese: 專有驅動是不可自由獲得或非開源的硬件驅動。

sentences.english: Yet this is the mentality behind the proprietary software model.
sentences.chinese: 然而，這就是專有軟件模式背後人們的心態。

sentences.english: At present, there are some scarcities in Proprietary copyright theory.
sentences.chinese: 目前，對專有出版權的認識上，在理論上存在不足。

sentences.english: Notice this word, it is a proper noun, so no article is needed.
sentences.chinese: 注意這個單詞是一個專有名詞，不用冠詞。

sentences.english: Proprietary ultra low loss solid core conductors.
sentences.chinese: 專有的超低消耗實芯導體。

sentences.english: They hold their shares in severalty.
sentences.chinese: 他們持有的是自己專有的股份。

sentences.english: The know-how of one system can be shuttled back and forth between separate species.
sentences.chinese: 一個系統的專有信息可以在不同的物種之間穿梭往返。

sentences.english: is the arbitary name of a destination created for the service.
sentences.chinese: 是爲該服務創建的目的文件的專有名稱。

sentences.english: A patent gives inventors exclusive rights to their inventions for a fixed period of time.
sentences.chinese: 專利授予發明者對其發明在一定時期內的專有權。

sentences.english: This measure may preclude the exclusive agency from selling crucial crude oil.
sentences.chinese: 這個措施可以使專有的代勞代理不克出售抉擇的原油。

sentences.english: "Google has never suggested that they want a proprietary ecosystem, " Pitz says.
sentences.chinese: 谷歌從未表示要建立一個專有的生態系統。

sentences.english: Proprietary ceramic tube sockets with silver contacts.
sentences.chinese: 專有的陶瓷管插座與銀接觸。

sentences.english: She granted a reporter an exclusive interview last week.
sentences.chinese: 上週她同意了一名記者的專有采訪。
